'''''Crosswize''''' is a [[shoot 'em up]] released by [[Firebird Software|Firebird]] in [[1988 in video gaming|1988]] for the [[ZX Spectrum]] home computer.  It was the sequel to ''[[Sidewize]]''.

==Plot==
The planet Luna is under attack by Mutants and must be defended.

==Overview==
The game is very similar to its predecessor, with a lone warrior battling waves of alien enemies. A notable difference is the ability to fire in both directions, as in ''[[Side Arms]]''. Again, power-ups may be collected for improved weapons and firepower.

==Development==
''Crosswize'' was published by [[Firebird Software]]. A sequel to ''[[Sidewize]]'', it was programmed by [[Steve Wetherill]] and [[Colin Grunes]], who designed the previous game.<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]|title=Previews|pages=116–117|issue=51|date=April 1988|url=https://archive.org/stream/crash-magazine-51/Crash_51_Apr_1988#page/n115/mode/2up}}</ref>

